1998 Toyota Starlet Glanza V - Japanese import.

Glanza V EP91 (1998 -1999)

This version uses the 4E-FTE 1331cc engine, producing 133bhp @ 6400rpm.  The car features a full bodykit, comprising of a front spoiler with integrated driving lamps, sideskirts, and a wrap-around rear spoiler.  A revision in 1998 included a re-styled front bumper, clear front indicators, revised rear light clusters and a more up-to-date interior.  Inside, the impressive specification includes a Drivers Airbag, ABS, Power Steering, Manual Climate Control & Air Conditioning, Electrically adjustable and retractable Door Mirrors, Power Windows and Central Door Locking.  Some cars have a different heating/air conditioning layout on the dashboard (either a manual dial or electronic push buttons).  White dials and a progressive turbo gauge (a series of lights indicate the stage of the turbos boost) complete the sporty theme.  A ‘dual-mode’ turbo setting via a button on the dashboard allows the driver to switch between 2 factory preset boost levels, offering 115bhp on low boost and 133bhp on high setting.  A limited, lightweight edition is also available, which foregoes some ‘creature comforts’ such as ABS, Electric Windows etc.  The car is available with automatic transmission or a 5-speed manual.  Due to its ability to keep up with cars from a higher class, the Japanese nicknamed the Glanza, ‘The Flyer’.

ITS VERY SPACIOUS, HAS LOTS OF LEG ROOM IN THE FRONT AND REAR AND A LARGE BOOT FOR ALL THE SHOPPING :) THE INTERIOR IS IN TOP CONDITION, WITH ITS MATCHING BLACK VALOUR SEATS AND ORIGINAL VW MATS ALL AROUND. I HAVE OWNED OTHER SMALL CARS IN THE PAST INCLUDING A PEUGEOT 206 AND A 2002 FORD FIESTA AND I CAN HONESTLY SAY, THE POLO IS OUT OF THEY'RE LEAGUE. THE BUILD QUALITY IS SECOND TO NONE, IT FEELS SO MUCH MORE SOLID THAN THE OTHER SMALL HATCHBACKS ON THE MARKET. IT DOESN'T FEEL FLIMSY NOR IS IT SWAYED BY THE SLIGHTEST BIT OF MOTORWAY CROSS WINDS AS SMALL CARS USUALLY TEND TO. YOU CAN REALLY FEEL THE GERMAN BUILD QUALITY. THE POLO IS MUCH SAFER THAN THE OTHER COMPETITORS IN THE MARKET, IT COMES WITH ABS, DRIVER AND PASSENGER AIRBAGS, FRONT SEAT SIDE IMPACT AIRBAGS AS WELL AS OTHER REFINEMENTS SUCH AS: • CENTRAL LOCKING, • POWER STEERING, • HEATING/ VENTILATION UNIT WITH 4 SPEED FAN, • CD RADIO/CASSETTE/RDS/4 SPEAKERS/ROOF AERIAL, • ISOFIX PREPERATION FOR 2 REAR CHILD SEATS, • ELECTRICALLY ADJUSTABLE HEATED DOOR MIRRORS, • HEATED REAR WINDOW, • BOSCH AERO FRONT AND REAR WIPERS WHICH ARE MUCH LAST LONGER LASTING THAN STANDARD WINDOW WIPERS AND PROVIDE A MUCH BETTER WIPE. IT HAS ALSO JUST HAD NEW FRONT BRAKE PADS FITTED LESS THAN 100 MILES AGO. BRAND NEW SPARE TYRE. JACK, SPANNER, LOCKING WHEEL NUT KEY ALL IN THE BOOT. THE BODYWORK IS IN OVERALL GREAT CONDITION, THE ODD MARK BUT NOTHING MAJOR AT ALL, JUST ME BEING FUSSY :) COLOUR CODED BUMPERS ALL ROUND. GENUINE REASON FOR SALE; IN NEED OF UNIVERSITY FUNDS :( I HAVE SPENT A LOT OF TIME AND CARE IN MY PRIDE AND JOY. I AM A KEEN VOLKSWAGEN ENTHUSIAST SO YOU CAN BE ASSURED THAT THE CAR HAS BEEN METICULOUSLY TAKEN CARE OF. IT HAS NEVER THRASHED AROUND OR ILL-TREATED. THE CAR HAS HAD NO EXPENSE SPARED IN TERMS OF MAINTENANCE AND IS REGULARLY VALETED INSIDE AND OUT. I CAN HONESTLY SAY IT HAS NEVER GIVEN ME ANY PROBLEMS AND HAS PROVEN TO BE AN EXTREMELY RELIABLE CAR, LIVING UP TO VOLKSWAGEN'S SPECTACULAR BUILD QUALITY. I'LL BE SAD TO SEE IT GO BUT I HOPE IT CAN GIVE SOMEONE ELSE THE JOY IT HAS GIVEN ME OVER THE SMALL AMOUNT OF TIME THAT I HAVE OWNED IT. THE PREVIOUS OWNERS HAD RECEIEVED THE CAR UNDER THE MOTABLIILTY SCHEME: A government run scheme to provide vehicles, wheelchairs and powered scooters to disabled people in the UK. description._content:
I stumbled upon a folder of pics from when I fitted the Reiger bodykit, Irmscher "M3 style" mirrors, Quad headlamp conversion and some other goodies.

This shot was always one of my favourites as it went about showing off the newly added goodies without having to show the whole of the car to do so.

I still love the colour that both my Astra's shares - Breeze Blue - it wasn't exactly a normal colour to see the Astra Coupe painted, and even rarer still in the Turbo edition.  When I ordered my 1.9CDTI Mk5 Astra Sportshatch I specifically asked for it in the same colour, and by heck they looked great sitting side by side on the driveway.

After initially spending the time and money under the lid on the engine I finally gave into fitting the Reiger kit in mid 2005 (car was new in 2002), and after this the car was featured in Total Vauxhall and had several smaller snaps and features in other magazines and newspapers.

Kia to Launch Sportier Forte Koup SX-R in Canada

The good: the new Kia Koup has just gotten a bit sportier as the Korean automaker has announced a new 'R' package with styling and performance accessories for the SX model. The bad: the 'R' package is available only to Canadian buyers

The aesthetics of the Koup are beefed up with a five-piece bodykit that includes a pair of front lip spoiler, chunky side skirts and a discreet boot lid spoiler. The two-door model's looks are complemented by a set of neat 18-inch alloy wheels wrapped in Yokohoma S-drive tires, and 'R' branded badges and door sills.

While the R treatment does nothing to the Koup SX's 173-horsepower 2.4-liter four-cylinder engine, it does add a sport exhaust, AEM air filter, new springs that lower the ride height by 1.3'' and a strut bar to improve handling.

The 'R' package will be available in Canada as a dealer-installed kit starting from mid-May.

Chevron GT3 (2012) Engine 3500cc Chevron/Langford V6 CHEVRON SET www.flickr.com/photos/45676495@N05/sets/72157623652508665... While based on the same design, as the GR8 the GT3 features sevral modifications to accomodate its larger 420bhp engine, This new engine is a bespoke V6 developed for Chevron by Langford. Displacing 3.5 litre, it is officially rated at 420 bhp. The all-aluminium unit is mated to a Hewland six-speed gearbox. The sequential 'box is operated through a paddle-shift system supplied by Shiftec. Like the GR8, the new GT3 uses a steel tubular spaceframe chassis with conventional double wishbone suspension. Among the changes are larger brakes to cope with the power of the larger engine. Revisions have also been made to the bodywork, which is wider to allow for bigger wheels and also sports additional air-intakes. A larger splitter and full-width rear wing are also part of new 'GT3' bodykit. A key requirement to homologate the new Chevron for the GT3 class it is obviously intended for, is a production road car, which has yet to be announced. The car has nevertheless been allowed to run in the invitation class of the British GT championship pending the homologation. In the June 2012 GT Cup race at Brands Hatch, works driver Jordan Witt managed to win all three races of the weekend. photo.title: 1994 Holden HSV VR Commodore Clubsport Sedan

description._content:
The VR Commodore was built from July 1993-April 1995. 
The VR was a major facelift on the 2nd generation Commodore, with only the doors and roof remaining unchanged. It got a smoother body with a new grille, the taillights were set up high.
Models available;
Executive, Acclaim, Berlina, Calais, S and SS 
The SS got 5.0 V8, full body kit, sports interior, FE2 suspension, alloys. The HSV cars were based on the SS.
HSV built performance versions for Holden, to make money for their race programme and to homologate parts for racing. 
The VR Clubsport was the base model at HSV.  A few tweaks were made to the 5.0 V8, it got a cold air intake, low restriction exhaust, adjustments to the computer giving it 185kw, also 5 spd manual, full body kit with very prominent rear spoiler and 17 in alloys. 
Other models were; 
GTS; next model up, bigger brakes, 215kw 5.7 V8 
Senator; based on the Berlina, luxury plus power.  
Maloo; HSV Utility, high performance V8 and bodykit
Engines; 130kw 3.8 V6 or 165kw 5.0 V8 (185kw HSV)

With the Rover Group only a few months away, this was the final car of from ARG. Powered by the Turbo charged 152bhp engine from the MG Montego, driving through a Honda gearbox, to create one of the quickest MGs ever, complete with torque steer. The model was a true wolf in sheeps clothing, but the Tickford designed bodykit and alloy wheels, did little to entice customers. A sleeping classic, the Maestro Turbo was dropped in 1991, as Rover had launched GTi versions of the new 200 and 400 models, though the standard Maestro remained in production until December 1994.. Although I've seen this before, it would be madness not to re-document 50% of all of the taxed 19 RSi's left on British roads. That's right, just two remain taxed and this is one of them. The RSi was much more popular in the cabriolet, the hatchback didn't really have a lot to offer alongside offerings from Ford, Vauxhall and VW at the time. 

Having said that, I really like the styling of the 19, it's neat and inoffensive. The RSi bodykit and styling features set it off nicely and it's a good colour also. It's been in current hands now since March 1999 which is a superb run and the owner is keeping it very tidy indeed. The mileage was around 129,000 in September when it was last put through its MOT.
